- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the design process of hypertext systems and how the model can support it, which is relevant to software engineering.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper mentions the close connection to logic-based development and verification, which is relevant to the field of logic in computer science.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper presents an algebraic specification of the hypertext reference model, which is relevant to the field of programming languages.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the development of hypertext since the WWW came up, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction.
